This doesn't really work for me. One interview was essentially  which has already been done a thousand times on this site (this was also present in the other interviews as well). One interview contains a 400-word recap of information that has already been disclosed to the reader.

I had no interest in these characters because it just felt like more of the same  I feel like there is a lot of ground to explore the ideas you're putting forth in this, but I don't think it's done in a particularly compelling way.

Also, as a side note, Tyranosaurus Flex is a distractingly dumb name for a glam rock band. It reads too much like the actual glam rock band T. Rex. Maybe that's what you were going for, but it's like having a fake British Invasion band called  or something.

The final bit is by far the strongest, because it actually shows a development of the character from anger to acceptance, which is kind of cool. If you focused more on the process whereby their anger becomes acceptance both of their containment and irrelevance, that would be something I would like to read. As is, -1.







